graph

Class UndirectedGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.Graph
      • graph.UndirectedGraph

  • public class UndirectedGraph
extends Graph
    Undirected graph represents graphs with edges that do not have a direction, example if a graph has two vertices (A, B) then an edge traversal for "A - B" would be bi-directional i.e. "A to B" and "B to A" are both allowed.
